Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (elevated creatinine), marked hyperbilirubinemia, metabolic acidosis (low pH, low pCO₂, low O₂ saturation), and dyslipidemia (high total and LDL cholesterol). Other parameters, including blood count and liver enzymes, are within normal limits. These findings suggest acute or chronic kidney and possible hepatobiliary dysfunction, with increased cardiovascular risk. Immediate clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
